100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 29, 1925, the League of Nations took a significant step by appointing a commission to investigate the ongoing situation in the Ruhr Valley, where tensions between France and Germany continue to simmer. In the United States, the nation grapples with economic shifts as the Stock Market shows signs of recovery, though concerns about inflation linger. Meanwhile, the British Parliament is poised to debate a contentious new bill aimed at reforming the tax system.
